<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-30T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-30T22:00:00-05:00" n="664" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11698: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ballantine</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-31T11:00:00+08:00">December 31, 1931—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 31—2:30
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have just been informed authoritatively that the necessary order for
                            the dissolution of the National Government at Canton on January 1st is
                            being issued today.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Nanking, Legation at Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ballantine</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>